(41, 10, 22, 55, 4, 10, 10, 'great possessions', 'Attachment to Worldly Possessions', 'This connection highlights the theme of attachment to worldly possessions and desires. In Mark, the man''s sadness stems from his great possessions, while in 2 Timothy, Demas forsakes Paul for love of the present world.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 10, 22, 26, 33, 31, 31, 'great possessions', 'Connection of Covetousness and Grief', 'Both passages emphasize the conflict between material wealth and spiritual commitment. The SOURCE verse highlights the man''s grief over his possessions, while the TARGET passage addresses the people''s love for their covetousness despite hearing the words of God.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
